        "question": "What drum kit did Lars Ulrich use on Metallica's Load?",
        "answer": "Lars Ulrich recorded Metallica's Load (1996) on a Tama Star Classic Maple kit — Tama's flagship maple series and an upgrade from the Artist Maple used on the Black Album (1991). The configuration was a 22\" bass drum driven by a double pedal, 10\" and 12\" rack toms, and 14\" and 16\" floor toms. The Star Classic's enhanced maple shell construction delivered greater warmth and resonance than the preceding Artist Maple, suited to Load's open, blues-influenced production approach. Bob Rock recorded the kit at The Plant Studios in Sausalito, California, with room microphones capturing the natural acoustic character of the shell rather than relying on the heavy gated reverb that defined the Black Album drum sound."
