      "description": "Lars's St. Anger-era cymbal setup was built around his longstanding Zildjian endorsement, blending the heavier, brighter Z Custom series with the more musical A Custom line. The Z Custom B20 alloy is computer-lathed for a consistently bright, projecting voice — well-suited to the close-miked, dry, frequency-dense St. Anger mix where cymbal frequencies needed to cut without the help of room ambience.\n\nThe 14\" A Custom hi-hats were a continuation of the hi-hat size Lars had used for years — the bright, defined articulation he relies on for fast pattern work and accent transitions. The crash array mixed Z Custom and A Custom voices: heavier Z Custom crashes for sharp, aggressive sectional accents matching the album's raw character, with A Custom 18\" providing a more musical crash voice for transitions that needed slightly more body.\n\nThe Z Custom 20\" ride and A Custom 18\" China rounded out the array. The Z Custom ride delivers the bright, cutting bell definition needed for the album's aggressive ride passages, while the A Custom China provides the trashy accent voice that punctuates St. Anger's frequent riff transitions and breakdown moments.",
