      "description": "Lars's cymbal setup for Hardwired blended the Zildjian A Custom series — his go-to range since the Death Magnetic era — with select Z Custom pieces for added weight. Zildjian has been Lars's endorsement since the Master of Puppets era, and by 2016 the A Custom range had become his established core, with Z Custom crashes added for tracks demanding extra projection.\n\nThe 14\" A Custom hi-hats remained the rhythmic anchor of the setup. Their tight, bright character cut through the densely layered guitars on tracks like \"Hardwired\" and \"Atlas, Rise!,\" delivering the kind of cutting 8th-note definition that uptempo thrash drumming requires. The A Custom's brilliant finish gave the hats a presence in the mix that traditional A Series hats lacked.\n\nThe crash array on Hardwired expanded slightly versus the Death Magnetic setup. A 16\" A Custom delivered fast accents, an 18\" Z Custom contributed heavier projection for major section endings, and a 19\" A Custom provided full-wash sustain for climactic moments throughout \"Spit Out the Bone\" and \"Halo on Fire.\" The Z Custom's heavier weight versus the A Custom gave Lars a wider dynamic palette than relying on a single series.\n\nThe 20\" A Custom Ride carried the rhythmic load during the ride-driven passages on \"Moth Into Flame\" and the instrumental sections of \"Halo on Fire,\" its clear bell definition cutting through the mix without sacrificing wash sustain. The 18\" A Custom China supplied the explosive, trashy accents that have been a Metallica signature since \"Master of Puppets\" — used for riff endings and dramatic punctuation throughout the album.\n\nThe brilliant finish across the A Custom range produced a slightly more aggressive attack profile than traditional A Series cymbals would have delivered — a tonal choice that matched Greg Fidelman's punchy, modern production approach at HQ.",
